President Uhuru Kenyatta is facing a backlash in his  Mount Kenya   backyard after his remarks telling off leaders over claims of neglecting the area sparked off angry reactions. In a show of defiance Bahati MP Kimani Ngunjiri led peaceful  demonstrations in Nakuru town to protest the president’s reference to leaders alleging his neglect of the region as ‘ Washenzi” with former Kiambu Governor William Kabogo asking  the president not to ignore the rising dissent in his backyard.  